$interpreted: Panther Chieftain: ...So, the Seahorse Chieftan really turned into a Bewitcher? No wonder she didn't show up for the meeting today.
Wolf Chieftain: I heard she's so embarrassed that she won't even set foot outside her house...
Turtle Chieftain: Ohh, such sin, such sin...
Yonghyeon: Hey, what's got you all zoned out?
Soohyeon: Hmm... I was just thinking about the last Trial of the Three Sects. It was here that...
Yonghyeon: Yeah. We can't gather in the Alliance Hall with all these monsters about.
Li Hwa: It can't be helped~ Everything's been happening so fast lately.
Li Hwa: But you're Chieftan of the Kyo Tribe now. You've got your ma's footsteps to follow in.
Soohyeon: ...I know.
Wolf Chieftain: So, who's this we've got here? What kind of Beast are you supposed to be?
Soohyeon: I'm Soohyeon...
Panther Chieftain: You don't look like much to me~ What do you think, Turts?
Turtle Chieftain: What's there to say? Come on, let's take this gatecrashing Bewitcher out!
Yonghyeon: How dare you! She's come to this meeting as the rightful representative of the Kyo Tribe!
Panther Chieftain: Looks like the rumors are true. Our little salamander friend here's all grown up after fighting a few battles. He's even raising his voice at us now~
Soohyeon: But Yonghyeon's done his best to help everyone fight off the monsters!
Panther Chieftain: That's a different kettle of fish. We've got too much to deal with now, what with all these Bewitchers and monsters running around.
Panther Chieftain: But you can forget about wiping away the sins you've committed as a Bewitcher, nevermind joining our sacred Alliance!
Soohyeon: *sob*...
Toyokuni: That's exactly what we need right now.
Wolf Chieftain: T-Toyokuni... It's been a while...
Toyokuni: It's imperative that we band together against these rampaging monsters. All investigations into your heinous treason shall be temporarily suspended.
Toyokuni: And don't believe that the Qilin and Bull Chieftans have died in battle. There's no proof of it. All responsibility must lie at their feet!
Turtle Chieftain: You little...! You're saying that Qing-Feng deceived us... Have you no respect for your elders?!
Turtle Chieftain: I'll teach you a lesson on behalf of all the Komainu Tribe!!
Shun: What's happening here!?
Juan-Yun: Toyokuni? Chief? What are you fighting for?
Li Hwa: You're just in time, Juan-Yun! Make them stop, this is no time to be turning against each other.
Juan-Yun: Me!? I'm just standing in for the Qilin Chieftan on my father's behalf. What right do I have to...
Li Hwa: Don't be so modest. With no Arbiter around, we're going to need someone to take care of running things.
Juan-Yun: Of course, but I wasn't about to volunteer myself...
Shun: We don't have time to squabble now. I understand your reluctance, Lord Juan-Yun, but you're the only one left who might be able to mediate!
Juan-Yun: ...Well, I have to persuade them first...
Juan-Yun: ...General Shun and I have arrived late. With all the chaos out there, I'm overjoyed to find everybody safe and well.
Juan-Yun: As things stand, the Alliance is too fragile to survive any schism or fracture.
Juan-Yun: So I must plead with you all... Put aside your differences, and let's all work together. Please!
Turtle Chieftain: Heheh... Since young Lord Juan-Yun has spoken...
Toyokuni: ...Enough. Juan-Yun's right.
Juan-Yun: Thank you! There's no time to lose. Let's get to work~
Yonghyeon: I'll be outside. If anybody makes any trouble for you, just call me.
Soohyeon: ...Okay! Thank you, Yonghyeon!
Li Hwa: So, everybody's following the young Lord's lead after all... Not that I'm surprised...
Yonghyeon: Yup. Because the very day the Udumbara was destroyed, he was holding the Arbiter's pendant in his hands. He was reborn.
Yonghyeon: It's said among the people that the Holy Dragon returned him to life, so that he could save the East from catastrophe...
Yonghyeon: However indirectly, the young Lord... would have come to harm because of me.
Yonghyeon: So I'm delighted to see he's safe and sound!
Li Hwa: ......
Yonghyeon: ...What? Is it something I said?
Li Hwa: No, nothing~ Let's go~
Li Hwa: (It's just... I'm getting too old for this. So you'd have me believe he was miraculously brought back to life, would you...)
